article.headline: Weber State 57, Elon University 50
article.story: ELON, N.C. (AP) -- Weber State rallied from a 20-point halftime deficit to beat Elon 57-50 on the road Monday night. Sharpshooting reserves David Patten and Brett Cox sparked Weber State, combining to score 42 points and hitting 7-of-9 3-point attempts. The starting five for the Wildcats (3-1) combined to score six points on 3-for-20 shooting, part of the reason Elon led 34-14 at the break. But after shooting 61 percent from the floor in the first half, the Phoenix lost its touch. They scored just 16 points in the second half while making 24 percent of its shots and missing all six 3-point attempts. Scottie Rice and Montell Watson scored 10 each to lead Elon (1-5). The Wildcats hit their stride as Elon slumped, making 70 percent of its second-half attempts from the floor and 6-of-7 3-point tries.
